1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,480
A code diff shows what an agent changed,

2
00:00:03,480 --> 00:00:06,813
but not which layered instructions governed the run

3
00:00:06,813 --> 00:00:10,418
or whether the session supports its validation claims.

4
00:00:10,418 --> 00:00:13,752
Codex Rule Ledger turns those supplied artifacts into

5
00:00:13,752 --> 00:00:16,815
an inspectable evidence ledger, always labeled as

6
00:00:16,815 --> 00:00:18,752
an unattested local capture.

7
00:00:18,826 --> 00:00:22,230
The demo reconstructs one launch-time chain from global

8
00:00:22,230 --> 00:00:24,635
scope to the working directory.

9
00:00:24,635 --> 00:00:28,189
This synthetic case includes global and project guidance,

10
00:00:28,189 --> 00:00:30,614
a fallback, a deeper override,

11
00:00:30,614 --> 00:00:34,296
and a candidate excluded by the byte limit.

12
00:00:34,296 --> 00:00:37,977
It never invents missing history from today's filesystem.

13
00:00:38,031 --> 00:00:41,546
Each observable instruction gets a source-linked state.

14
00:00:41,546 --> 00:00:44,142
A successful test is supported.

15
00:00:44,142 --> 00:00:46,899
A failed typecheck followed by completion

16
00:00:46,899 --> 00:00:49,036
is contradicted by evidence.

17
00:00:49,036 --> 00:00:53,630
A missing build event is not evidenced, not failed.

18
00:00:53,630 --> 00:00:57,007
An untriggered documentation rule is not applicable,

19
00:00:57,007 --> 00:00:59,603
and subjective prose is declined.

20
00:00:59,603 --> 00:01:04,037
The inspector exposes the exact source and event anchors.

21
00:01:04,127 --> 00:01:07,823
Export preserves every source, result, evidence link,

22
00:01:07,823 --> 00:01:10,120
input hash, and warning.

23
00:01:10,120 --> 00:01:12,875
The filename is bound to the

24
00:01:12,875 --> 00:01:15,010
canonical SHA-256 ledger digest.

25
00:01:15,010 --> 00:01:18,386
Those hashes bind supplied bytes after capture;

26
00:01:18,386 --> 00:01:21,302
they do not authenticate the capture,

27
00:01:21,302 --> 00:01:24,516
prove trusted time, or guarantee obedience.

28
00:01:24,571 --> 00:01:28,014
Version zero point two adds a local CLI

29
00:01:28,014 --> 00:01:30,015
for already-normalized Audit Bundles.

30
00:01:30,015 --> 00:01:33,457
Recorded analysis is the keyless default and never

31
00:01:33,457 --> 00:01:35,458
reads an API key.

32
00:01:35,458 --> 00:01:38,900
This second synthetic case crosses the same deterministic

33
00:01:38,900 --> 00:01:42,493
audit seam, produces six records across five outcome

34
00:01:42,493 --> 00:01:45,376
classes, writes a private no-clobber file,

35
00:01:45,376 --> 00:01:47,958
and proves the engine is not

36
00:01:47,958 --> 00:01:49,959
hard-coded to one topology.

37
00:01:50,031 --> 00:01:54,774
Codex independently selected this problem, scoped both releases,

38
00:01:54,774 --> 00:01:58,236
and made the key architecture decision:

39
00:01:58,236 --> 00:02:01,152
GPT should understand instruction semantics,

40
00:02:01,152 --> 00:02:04,777
while deterministic code must own truth.

41
00:02:04,777 --> 00:02:08,239
It implemented each vertical test-driven slice,

42
00:02:08,239 --> 00:02:12,982
drove adversarial review repairs, deployed the keyless demo,

43
00:02:12,982 --> 00:02:15,517
and packaged this submission.

44
00:02:15,517 --> 00:02:20,804
Dan retained credentials, spend, eligibility, and publication authority.

45
00:02:20,804 --> 00:02:25,520
GPT-5.6 maps complete instruction lines into source-linked observable

46
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:30,099
proposals; TypeScript owns discovery, hashes, evidence sufficiency,

47
00:02:30,099 --> 00:02:32,634
and every final verdict.

48
00:02:32,634 --> 00:02:37,758
Official feedback, metadata-only Langfuse, reviewed Git, green CI,

49
00:02:37,758 --> 00:02:42,119
and production receipts corroborate that workflow without attesting

50
00:02:42,119 --> 00:02:45,581
prompts, reasoning, or individual edits.

51
00:02:45,650 --> 00:02:48,648
Codex Rule Ledger does not promise compliance.

52
00:02:48,648 --> 00:02:50,744
It gives reviewers a compact,

53
00:02:50,744 --> 00:02:53,623
runnable account of what supplied evidence supports,

54
00:02:53,623 --> 00:02:57,150
what it contradicts, and what it cannot prove.
